In another development, the Senate President, Dr Ahmad Ibrahim Lawan announced the Senate standing Committee shortly before he adjourned sitting until 24th September, 2019. The 69 committees in number, cut across party divides with Senators of the opposition political parties heading strategic Committees.  The Senate President revealed that the announcement was for Committee Chairmen and their deputies, while Committee membership were still being fine-tuned. Some of the committees are Appropriation which is chaired by Barau Jibrin; Finance, Adeola Olamilekan; Police, Dauda Jika; Defence, Aliyu Magatakarda Wammako and Army, Ali Ndume, NDDC, Peter Nwabaoshi; Agriculture, Abdullahi Adamu and INEC, Kabiru Gaya and others.